item.title: Police stop illegal anti-mask rally
item.description: A planned anti-mask rally in Melbourne in defiance of strict stage four lockdown laws fizzled out after only a few dozen people attended and were pounced on by waiting police.

item.title: Positive case at Catholic church mass
item.description: NSW Health has issued an alert after a positive coronavirus case attended mass on two occasions at a church in Sydney’s north west.

item.title: Man injured in ‘crossbow attack’
item.description: A man has been taken to hospital after he was allegedly shot with a crossbow in Sydney’s south west.

item.title: Victoria records 394 new cases
item.description: Victoria has recorded 394 new cases of coronavirus overnight and 17 deaths including 10 linked to aged care home outbreaks.

item.title: Ten new cases in NSW
item.description: NSW has recorded 10 new cases of coronavirus overnight, including two mystery cases with no known source.

item.title: Queensland records no new coronavirus cases
item.description: Queensland has recorded no new coronavirus cases in the last 24 hours, the Premier has revealed on Sunday morning.

item.title: ‘We’ve been flexible’: JobKeeper change possible
item.description: Finance Minister Mathias Cormann has said Australia needs to taper its reliance on JobKeeper and JobSeeker payments, as the country’s debt estimates mount to more than $850 billion.

item.title: Man stabbed on suburban street
item.description: A man was stabbed in the abdomen after a car full of people pulled up to him on an Adelaide street on Sunday morning.

item.title: Protests erupt in Lebanon
item.description: Protests have erupted across Lebanon on Saturday, as disdain for the country’s government grows following the deadly explosion on Tuesday which killed more than 150 people.

item.title: Sydney school student tests positive
item.description: A school in Sydney’s west will close for cleaning as it works to find close contacts of a student who tested positive to coronavirus.
